div.lvmaindiv
  div.container-fluid
    div.row
      div.col-xs-12
        h1 #{title}
    div.row
      div.col-xs-12.col-ld-6.col-ld-offset-3
        ul LongView is a simple web/IoT/whatever-app that lets you:
          li get real-time temperature and air pressure sensor data stream from a remote unit
          li get near real-time imagery captured by a webcam on that remote unit
          li pan the webcam left and right to look around
        br
        The remote unit can be a single-board computer ( Raspberry Pi / pcDuino / BeagleBoneBlack etc ), desktop or laptop. Just as long as it runs Node.js and has a USB port for communicating with an Arduino. Have fun! :)
        br
    div.row.lvmaindiv
      div.col-xs-5.col-xs-offset-1.col-md-4.col-md-offset-0
        form(ng-controller='HomeCtrl')
          p Username: 
            input(type="text" ng-model="username")
          p Password: 
            input(type="password" ng-model="userpassw")
          button.btn.btn-primary(ng-click="attemptLogin()", type="submit") Login      

